<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="type locality">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type locality.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Turkey, Artvin Province, Camili Village, Merata Plateau, unnamed mountain stream; 
<geoCoordinate degrees="41" direction="north" minutes="26" orientation="latitude" precision="15" seconds="30" value="41.44167">41°26'30&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
/
<geoCoordinate degrees="42" direction="east" minutes="04" orientation="longitude" precision="15" seconds="41" value="42.078056">42°04'41&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
; 2190 m a.s.l.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
North-eastern Turkey, Georgia (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 36" captionStartId="F36" captionText="Figure 36. Geographical (left) and vertical (right) distribution of Epeorus (Caucasiron) turcicus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure36" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471958" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">36</figureCitation>
). Known only from few sites in the Camili (Machakheli) District in Turkey and central Georgia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Larvae inhabit small streams at middle and high altitudes. Altitudinal range of sampling sites 928-2388 m a.s.l. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 36" captionStartId="F36" captionText="Figure 36. Geographical (left) and vertical (right) distribution of Epeorus (Caucasiron) turcicus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure36" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471958" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">36</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="main morphological diagnostics of larvae">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Main morphological diagnostics of larvae.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
(i) femora with medial hypodermal spot (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 37" captionStartId="F37" captionText="Figure 37. Epeorus (Caucasiron) turcicus, larva: A habitus in dorsal view B habitus in ventral view C habitus in lateral view D head of male in dorsal view E head of female in dorsal view F middle leg in dorsal view G abdominal terga (arrows point on dorso-posteriorly extended lateral stripes) H abdominal sterna II-VI I gill VII (in natural position from ventral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure37" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471959" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">37F</figureCitation>
); (ii) abdominal terga V-VII with stripe-like medial macula with lateral stripes extended dorso-posteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 37" captionStartId="F37" captionText="Figure 37. Epeorus (Caucasiron) turcicus, larva: A habitus in dorsal view B habitus in ventral view C habitus in lateral view D head of male in dorsal view E head of female in dorsal view F middle leg in dorsal view G abdominal terga (arrows point on dorso-posteriorly extended lateral stripes) H abdominal sterna II-VI I gill VII (in natural position from ventral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure37" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471959" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">37G</figureCitation>
, arrows); (iii) abdominal sterna without coloration pattern, nerve ganglia often coloured (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 37" captionStartId="F37" captionText="Figure 37. Epeorus (Caucasiron) turcicus, larva: A habitus in dorsal view B habitus in ventral view C habitus in lateral view D head of male in dorsal view E head of female in dorsal view F middle leg in dorsal view G abdominal terga (arrows point on dorso-posteriorly extended lateral stripes) H abdominal sterna II-VI I gill VII (in natural position from ventral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure37" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471959" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">37B, H</figureCitation>
); (iv) gill plates VII (in natural position from ventral view) narrow (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 37" captionStartId="F37" captionText="Figure 37. Epeorus (Caucasiron) turcicus, larva: A habitus in dorsal view B habitus in ventral view C habitus in lateral view D head of male in dorsal view E head of female in dorsal view F middle leg in dorsal view G abdominal terga (arrows point on dorso-posteriorly extended lateral stripes) H abdominal sterna II-VI I gill VII (in natural position from ventral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure37" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471959" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">37I</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 38" captionStartId="F38" captionText="Figure 38. Epeorus (Caucasiron) turcicus, larva: A labrum (left half in dorsal view right half in ventral view) B incisors of left mandible C incisors of right mandible D setae on dorsal surface of femora E surface and posterior margin of abdominal tergum VII F gill I G gill III H gill VII (flattened on slide) I-K gill VII (in natural position from ventral view) variability in shape L abdominal segments VIII-X in lateral view M sternum IX of female." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure38" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471960" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">38H-K</figureCitation>
); (v) setae on abdominal terga hair-like like (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 38" captionStartId="F38" captionText="Figure 38. Epeorus (Caucasiron) turcicus, larva: A labrum (left half in dorsal view right half in ventral view) B incisors of left mandible C incisors of right mandible D setae on dorsal surface of femora E surface and posterior margin of abdominal tergum VII F gill I G gill III H gill VII (flattened on slide) I-K gill VII (in natural position from ventral view) variability in shape L abdominal segments VIII-X in lateral view M sternum IX of female." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure38" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471960" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">38E</figureCitation>
); (vi) tergum X without postero-lateral projections (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 38" captionStartId="F38" captionText="Figure 38. Epeorus (Caucasiron) turcicus, larva: A labrum (left half in dorsal view right half in ventral view) B incisors of left mandible C incisors of right mandible D setae on dorsal surface of femora E surface and posterior margin of abdominal tergum VII F gill I G gill III H gill VII (flattened on slide) I-K gill VII (in natural position from ventral view) variability in shape L abdominal segments VIII-X in lateral view M sternum IX of female." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure38" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471960" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">38L</figureCitation>
); (vii) gill plates III with well-developed projection (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 38" captionStartId="F38" captionText="Figure 38. Epeorus (Caucasiron) turcicus, larva: A labrum (left half in dorsal view right half in ventral view) B incisors of left mandible C incisors of right mandible D setae on dorsal surface of femora E surface and posterior margin of abdominal tergum VII F gill I G gill III H gill VII (flattened on slide) I-K gill VII (in natural position from ventral view) variability in shape L abdominal segments VIII-X in lateral view M sternum IX of female." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure38" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471960" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">38G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
